---

```
Build a single Python script: find_internships.py
Location: e:\intraget\iib-india\backend\scripts\find_internships.py

PURPOSE:
Search internship websites → verify companies → filter paid only →
build clean Excel file → auto-expire old entries → output .xlsx

---

TECH STACK (pip install these, all free):
- httpx (async HTTP)
- openpyxl (Excel writing)
- python-whois (domain age)
- beautifulsoup4 (HTML parsing)
- python-dotenv (env vars)
- rich (terminal progress display)

---

INTERNSHIP SOURCES (in order of priority):

SOURCE 1 — Adzuna API (free, 1000 req/day)
Base URL: https://api.adzuna.com/v1/api/jobs/in/search/1
Params:
  app_id = ADZUNA_APP_ID from .env
  app_key = ADZUNA_API_KEY from .env
  results_per_page = 50
  what = "<domain keyword> intern"
  content-type = application/json
For each of 6 domains use these search keywords:
  Android App Development → "android developer intern"
  Game Development → "game developer intern unity unreal"
  iOS App Development → "ios developer intern swift"
  Web Development → "web developer intern frontend backend"
  Graphic Design → "graphic design intern ui designer"
  Data Science → "data science intern machine learning"

SOURCE 2 — Internshala (scrape public listings, no login)
URL: https://internshala.com/internships/<keyword>-internship/
Keywords per domain:
  Android → android-development
  Game Dev → game-development
  iOS → ios-development
  Web Dev → web-development
  Graphic Design → graphic-designing
  Data Science → data-science
Scrape: company name, stipend, title, duration, last date, apply link, location
Use httpx + BeautifulSoup. 5s timeout. On any error → skip, log, continue.

SOURCE 3 — Unstop (scrape public listings)
URL: https://unstop.com/internships?domain=<keyword>
Scrape same fields as Internshala.
On any error → skip, log, continue.

---

DOMAINS (exactly these 6, no others):
TARGET_DOMAINS = [
  "Android App Development",
  "Game Development",
  "iOS App Development",
  "Web Development",
  "Graphic Design",
  "Data Science"
]

EXCEL SHEET TABS:
Active tabs (one per domain):
  "APP ANDROID", "Game development", "APP IOS",
  "WEB DEVELOPMENT", "Graphic Design", "DATA SCIENCE"
Plus these tabs always:
  "NEEDS REVIEW", "REJECTED", "EXPIRED"

---

EXCEL COLUMN FORMAT (all tabs use same columns A-I):
A: Sr. No.
B: Company Name
C: Stipend
D: Name of internship
E: Duration
F: Role
G: Last Date  (format: "DD Mon YYYY" or "Not mentioned")
H: Link       (use openpyxl hyperlink — NEVER write plain text "LINK" without real URL)
I: Location

Sr. No. must be recalculated cleanly per tab (1,2,3... no gaps).

---

PIPELINE — run in this EXACT order for every internship found:

STEP 1: NORMALIZE
  - Parse stipend: extract number from "₹5000/month", "5k", "5,000 pm"
    → store as stipend_min (int), stipend_display (string)
  - Parse location: normalize
    "WFH"/"Remote"/"Work from home" → "Work from home"
    "Onsite"/"On-Site"/"(On-Site)" → "On-site"
    city names → keep as-is
  - Parse last_date: convert any date string to datetime object
  - Extract role: shorten internship title to clean role name
    "Flutter Developer - Internship" → "Flutter Developer Intern"
    "Unity FX Artist (VFX) – Mobile Game Project" → "Unity FX Artist (VFX)"

STEP 2: PAID GATE
  - stipend_min must be > 0
  - OR stipend_display contains "interview basis" (medium confidence)
  - FAIL → status = "REJECTED", reason = "unpaid_or_missing_stipend"
  - HARD STOP if fail

STEP 3: FRAUD DETECTION
  Scan title + description for these keywords:
    "training fee", "registration fee", "security deposit",
    "certificate fee", "joining fee", "pay to work",
    "pay to apply", "investment required", "refundable deposit",
    "refer and earn", "mlm", "downline", "earn from home"
  ANY match → status = "REJECTED", reason = "fraud_keyword:<keyword>"
  HARD STOP if match found

STEP 4: LINK VALIDATION
  async HTTP GET apply_link with 8s timeout, follow redirects
  FAIL conditions:
    - HTTP 4xx/5xx response
    - Final URL domain is wa.me or t.me or bit.ly
    - Connection timeout
    - Redirect to unrelated domain (not company domain + not known ATS)
  KNOWN ATS DOMAINS (auto-pass):
    internshala.com, linkedin.com, naukri.com, unstop.com,
    wellfound.com, lever.co, greenhouse.io, workday.com,
    smartrecruiters.com, ashbyhq.com, workindia.in
  PASS → apply_link_valid = True
  FAIL → status = "REJECTED", reason = "invalid_link:<reason>"
  HARD STOP if fail

STEP 5: COMPANY VERIFICATION
  Run all these checks. Each check = 1 signal if passes.
  Infrastructure failure (timeout/error) = 0 signal, NOT -1 signal.

  CHECK 1 — Website exists (httpx GET company domain, 5s timeout)
    Pass: 2xx response → signal +1
    Fail: 4xx/5xx/timeout → signal +0 (infra failure, not fraud)

  CHECK 2 — Website has real pages (scrape homepage links)
    Pass: has /about OR /careers OR /contact in links → signal +1
    Fail: no such pages → signal +0

  CHECK 3 — Apply link on known ATS
    Pass: apply_link domain in KNOWN_ATS_DOMAINS → signal +1
    Fail: unknown domain → signal +0

  CHECK 4 — LinkedIn company page exists
    HTTP GET https://www.linkedin.com/company/<company-name-slug>
    Pass: 200 response → signal +1
    Fail: 404 → signal +0

  CHECK 5 — Domain age (python-whois)
    age >= 365 days → signal +1
    age 90-365 days → signal +0
    age < 90 days → signal -1 (active negative)
    whois timeout → signal +0 (infra failure)

  CHECK 6 — Internshala company page exists
    HTTP GET https://internshala.com/companies/<slug>/
    Pass: 200 → signal +1
    Fail: 404 → signal +0

  CHECK 7 — Glassdoor company exists
    HTTP GET https://www.glassdoor.co.in/Reviews/<slug>-Reviews
    Pass: 200 → signal +1
    Fail: → signal +0

  CHECK 8 — Google Maps / Places name search (free tier)
    Only if GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY set in .env
    Found company with reviews → signal +1
    Not found / key missing → signal +0

  trust_score = sum of signals (min 0, max 8)
  
  DECISION:
    trust_score >= 4 → company_status = "VERIFIED"
    trust_score 2-3  → company_status = "NEEDS_REVIEW"
    trust_score <= 1 → company_status = "REJECTED", reason = "low_trust"

  If REJECTED → status = "REJECTED", HARD STOP

STEP 6: DEADLINE CHECK
  today = datetime.today().date()
  If last_date is set AND last_date < today:
    → status = "EXPIRED", reason = "deadline_passed"
    → move to EXPIRED tab, STOP
  If last_date is None:
    → mark as "Not mentioned", set default_expiry = today + 60 days
    → if created_at + 60 days < today → status = "EXPIRED"

STEP 7: DEDUPLICATION
  hash = SHA256(company_name.lower() + title.lower() + domain)
  Check against seen_hashes set (in-memory per run)
  If duplicate → skip silently

STEP 8: WRITE TO EXCEL
  All checks passed → write to correct domain tab
  status = "REJECTED" for any step → write to REJECTED tab with reason
  status = "EXPIRED" → write to EXPIRED tab
  company_status = "NEEDS_REVIEW" → write to NEEDS REVIEW tab
  
  REJECTED tab extra columns: + "Rejection Reason" + "Checked At"
  EXPIRED tab extra columns: + "Expired At"
  NEEDS REVIEW tab extra columns: + "Reason" + "Checked At"

---

EXCEL FORMATTING (openpyxl):

Header row (row 1):
  - Background: #1A1A1E (dark)
  - Font color: #F5A623 (amber)
  - Font bold: True
  - Font: Calibri 11

Data rows:
  - Alternating: #0D0D0F and #141417
  - Font color: #F8F8F8
  - Font: Calibri 10

Link column (H):
  - Use ws.cell().hyperlink = apply_link
  - Display text = "Apply" 
  - Font color: #F5A623, underline: True
  - NEVER write plain text without hyperlink

Column widths:
  A(Sr.No.)=8, B(Company)=25, C(Stipend)=22,
  D(Name)=40, E(Duration)=12, F(Role)=28,
  G(LastDate)=14, H(Link)=10, I(Location)=18

Freeze row 1 (header always visible).
Auto-filter on all columns.

